body_html: Thanks caisq!I just find the bug, it takes me about two days. tfdbg is really powerful tools, I find it is indeed cause by my feature extraction when i move action on images! This tools really amazing for us to debug tensorflow. By the way, when I use this tfdbg, it seems when I need to save the model and also using tfdbg, it will report: ufunc"is nan" not supported for the input types, and the inputs could not be safely coerced to any supported types according to the casting rule"safe". I guess it is the filter problem, not about the tfdbg itself. Any suggestions about define this filter to avoid this problems?
